Never leave cooking food unattended on the stove, as this is a leading cause of residential fires. Always turn off the burners before you leave the kitchen for any reason.
Avoid wearing loose-fitting clothing when you are cooking near an open flame. Long sleeves can easily catch fire if they come into contact with a burner or hot surface.
There is a person carrying a large crowbar walking through the quiet residential alleyway. They are checking the locks on every single garage door as they pass by the houses.
Check the notice board in the lobby to see the updated map of all emergency meeting points. Knowing exactly where to go can save precious time during a real fire.
