Always ask someone if they are finished with a machine before you start moving their plates. Communication is key to maintaining a friendly and respectful environment for all gym members here.
Make sure to unload the barbell completely after you finish your last set. Leaving plates on the bar is inconvenient for the next user who might be lifting much less weight.
Using a spotter is great, but make sure you ask someone who is not currently in the middle of their own intense set. Respect their time and their workout flow today.
