The overhead press is a classic strength movement. It requires a lot of core stability to push the barbell from your shoulders up toward the ceiling without losing your balance.
Russian twists are perfect for working the obliques. I sit on the floor, lean back slightly, and rotate my torso from side to side while holding a small weight plate.
Goblet squats are easier for beginners to learn the correct form. You hold a single dumbbell close to your chest like a cup while performing a standard deep squat movement.
